snippet.textDisplay: I haven't seen much from Wes Anderson and honestly I'm not a fan of his work based on what I have seen. Currently I have only seen The Grand Budapest Hotel and Fantastic Mr Fox (which I saw a very long time ago when it came out). I do plan to watch the rest of his filmography because I'm interested in what he has to offer and I'm willing to get through it even if I don't enjoy his films. But from this trailer, the style and the way it's structured and presented. Is this exactly what Wes Anderson films are always like?
snippet.textOriginal: I haven't seen much from Wes Anderson and honestly I'm not a fan of his work based on what I have seen. Currently I have only seen The Grand Budapest Hotel and Fantastic Mr Fox (which I saw a very long time ago when it came out). I do plan to watch the rest of his filmography because I'm interested in what he has to offer and I'm willing to get through it even if I don't enjoy his films. But from this trailer, the style and the way it's structured and presented. Is this exactly what Wes Anderson films are always like?
